#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pre-requisites
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"IFoam" is a OpenFOAM based interactive engineering environment requires the
 following mandatory and optional pre-requisites.

* Make sure that confFoam (common configuration package) is installed 
  Can be found at https://csrcs.pbmr.co.za/svn/nea/prototypes/reaktor/conffoam.
  Please follow instructions from corresponding INSTALL file to setup confFoam
  in your environment.

* Make sure that OpenFOAM is installed (tested with versions 1.4.1-dev and 1.6).
  Please follow instructions from corresponding INSTALL file to setup OpenFOAM
  in your environment.

* Make sure that pyFoam is installed (tested with release 7.4)
  Can be found at https://csrcs.pbmr.co.za/svn/nea/prototypes/reaktor/pyfoam.
  Please follow instructions from corresponding INSTALL file to setup pyFoam
  in your environment.

* Make sure that Python (developement version, with Python.h header file) is 
  installed (tested with 2.4, 2.6.2) with corresponding Tkinter package
  Please follow instructions from http://www.python.org/ web-site.

* Make sure that IPython is installed (tested with releases 0.9.1 & 0.10)
  Please follow instructions from http://www.ipython.scipy.org/ web-site.

* Install foam2vtk (optional)
  Can be found at https://csrcs.pbmr.co.za/svn/nea/prototypes/reaktor/foam2vtk.
  Please follow instructions from corresponding INSTALL file to setup foam2vtk
  in your environment.

* Install unv2foam (optional)
  Can be found at https://csrcs.pbmr.co.za/svn/nea/prototypes/reaktor/unv2foam.
  Please follow instructions from corresponding INSTALL file to setup unv2foam
  in your environment.

* Install unv2foam (optional)
  Can be found at https://csrcs.pbmr.co.za/svn/nea/prototypes/reaktor/unv2foam.
  Please follow instructions from corresponding INSTALL file to setup unv2foam
  in your environment.

* Install Python Pmw library (optional) (tested with 1.3.2 )
  Please follow instructions from http://www.pmw.sourceforge.net/ web-site.

Then follow below instructions in order to build and install the "IFoam".


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Basic Installation
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The build procedure of the "IFoam" package is based on GNU autoconf and make utilities. 
In order to build the module you have to perform the following actions:

1. Go to the source directory:

   cd <path to the sources>

2. Modify the provided "env.sh" file to adjust to your local environment.
   
   <your favorite editor> ./env.sh

3. Source this "env.sh" file to define corresponding build environment.

   source ./env.sh

4. Configuring the "IFoam" build system:

   ./build_configure
   ./configure

   Make sure that after each configuration step the "--- OK ---" message is
   printed in your console.

   To see all applicable configuration options run "./configure --help"
   Currently, the following options are available:

     --with-pyfoam=<path>
     --with-foam2vtk=<path>
     --with-unv2foam=<path>
     --with-foam2med=<path>
     --with-foam2vtk=<path>
     --with-unv2foam=<path>


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"IFoam" environment
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Before start to use "IFoam" it is necessary to source the generated "bashrc" file


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"IFoam" installation check
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Run the following "IFoam" script

  ./IFoam/examples/run_examples


